Package uk.msci.project.rsa

Enum Class DigestType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<DigestType>
uk.msci.project.rsa.DigestType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<DigestType>, Constable
public enum DigestType extends Enum<DigestType>
Enum representing the various cryptographic hash functions supported in the digital signature schemes. This enumeration facilitates the selection and use of different hash functions, including SHA-256, SHA-512, and SHAKE variants, in the context of cryptographic operations.

    • SHA_256

      public static final DigestType SHA_256
      SHA-256 hash function. Provides a standard cryptographic hash function with a fixed output size of 256 bits.

    • SHA_512

      public static final DigestType SHA_512
      SHA-512 hash function. Offers a cryptographic hash function with a fixed output size of 512 bits, providing a higher level of security than SHA-256.

    • SHAKE_128

      public static final DigestType SHAKE_128
      SHAKE-128 hash function. A member of the SHA-3 family of hash functions, capable of producing variable-length output. SHAKE-128 is designed for flexibility and security.

    • SHAKE_256

      public static final DigestType SHAKE_256
      SHAKE-256 hash function. Similar to SHAKE-128, this hash function is part of the SHA-3 family and can produce a variable-length output but with a higher security level than SHAKE-128.

    • MGF_1_SHA_256

      public static final DigestType MGF_1_SHA_256
      MGF1 with SHA-256 hash function. Represents a mask generation function using SHA-256. It's often used in cryptographic protocols requiring data masking with a hash function like SHA-256.

    • MGF_1_SHA_512

      public static final DigestType MGF_1_SHA_512
      MGF1 with SHA-512 hash function. Similar to MGF1 with SHA-256 but utilizes SHA-512 for cryptographic operations requiring a higher security level.

    • getDigestTypeFromCustomString

      public static DigestType getDigestTypeFromCustomString(String s)
      Converts a custom string representation of a hash function into its corresponding DigestType enum value. This method is particularly useful for parsing string inputs (such as from a configuration file or user input) into the defined hash function types.
      Parameters:
      s - The string representation of the digest type. Expected values include "SHA-256", "SHA-512", "SHAKE-128", "SHAKE-256", "SHA-256 with MGF1", and "SHA-512 with MGF1".
      Returns:
      The corresponding DigestType enum value if the input string matches any known digest type, or null if there is no match.
